There are multiples ways to choose colours for webpages.

1. Indicate the color name (
example :
background-color: red;
background-color: yellow;
background-color: blue;

NOTE: Our browsers support 140 standard colour names

2. Using rgb() values, it stands for RED GREEN BLUE, which consist three color values

rgb(255, 0, 0) will give you red
rgb(0, 255, 0) will give you GREEN
rgb(0, 0, 255 ) will give you BLUE
rgb(255, 255, 255) will give you WHITE
- Each value defines the intensity of the color between 0 to 255

IN CSS3 version it specifies the opacity for colors and the method is called, rgba()
-the argument range should be 0 to 1

rgb (255,0,0)  RED
rgba(255,0,0,0.5) RED but will have the red colour decreased to opacity twice the color

3. Using the Hexadecimal values

#ff0000 - RED
#00ff00: green;
#0000ff- blue
#ffffff -white , it has the  highest intensity
#000000 - black, has the lowest intensity
